# data-agent-core

Framework for building methodology-aware data agents on Trino/Iceberg with structured reasoning, MLflow tracing, and 7-dimension evaluation.

## What This Is

A pip-installable Python package that extracts the shared architecture from two production data agents (MLB and NNDSS) into reusable factory functions. Domain projects are thin — they import shared code and configure it via a single `agent-config.yaml`.

**Key innovations preserved:**
- **MCP enrichment contract** — every tool response includes methodology, caveats, supported/unsupported conclusions
- **Reasoning rubric injector** — 6-step `<reasoning>` block with deterministic confidence cards (HIGH/MODERATE/LOW from tool trace)
- **7-dimension capability evaluation** — cross_dataset_reasoning, methodology_awareness, scope_adherence, causal_inference_boundaries, geographic_resolution, terminology_fluency, confidence_calibration

## Quick Start

```bash
# Install
pip install -e ".[all]"

# Scaffold a new domain agent
data-agent init my-domain

# Configure
cd my-domain
# Edit agent-config.yaml, system_prompt.md, add data files

# Validate
data-agent validate

# Run tests
data-agent test

# Build and deploy
make build && make push && make deploy-all
```

## Architecture

```
data-agent-core (pip package)
├── config/       — Pydantic v2 DomainConfig + YAML loader
├── agent/        — Chainlit + LangGraph lifecycle (create_agent_app)
├── tools/        — Tool factories (query_trino, describe_datasets, etc.)
├── mcp/          — FastMCP server factory (create_mcp_server)
├── mlflow/       — MLflow init, CA bundle, autolog
├── prompts/      — System prompt registry with MLflow integration
├── eval/         — KFP pipeline, 4+7 scorers, predictor function
├── testing/      — pytest fixtures (mock_trino, mock_spicedb)
└── deploy/       — Containerfile and kustomize templates
```

## Generated Project Structure

```
my-domain/
├── agent-config.yaml              # THE config file
├── system_prompt.md               # Domain reasoning prompt
├── agents/my-domain-agent/app.py  # ~10 lines
├── agents/my-domain-mcp-server/   # ~10 lines
├── evaluations/                   # KFP pipeline + seed questions
├── tests/                         # Hermetic tests
├── data/                          # Your parquet/CSV files
└── Makefile                       # build, push, deploy
```

## Examples

See `examples/nndss/` and `examples/mlb/` for complete domain configurations.

